# ============================================================
# MARKET CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: market
scope: market.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for market.

## policy_rules
Market policy constrains:
- who may list
- what may be listed
- when listings are visible
- who may see which details
- when listings must be restricted or hidden

## required_behavior
- listing eligibility must be explicit
- visibility scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit
- policy escalation must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public summary listing
- restricted detail listing
- operator detail listing
- reviewer detail listing
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow bounded public visibility for allowed listings
- allow restricted detail only for allowed actors
- deny hidden authority claims through listings
- deny source-truth overwrite by market projection
- deny out-of-policy listing exposure

## escalation_rules
If source truth,
listing authority,
policy scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the listing path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- eligibility is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
- escalation rules are explicit
